# Copy to .env.local and add your API key for AI maze generation (local / Vercel only).
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your_key_here
# OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key_here
#
# Hot-seat multiplayer (up to 4 humans) ships in every build — no env flag required.
#
# itch.io: npm run package:itch → dist/creep-labyrinth-itch.zip (HTML upload).
# CrazyGames: npm run package:crazygames → dist/creep-labyrinth-crazygames.zip (HTML5 upload).
# Static uploads have no API; "Generate with AI" falls back to a random maze.

# itch.io: run `npm run package:itch` — static build has no /api; use Random maze or host with API keys.
#
# Client crash / error logs → server (Next with /api only; static zips have no ingest endpoint).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLIENT_LOG_INGEST=1
# CLIENT_LOG_INGEST_SECRET=long-random-string
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLIENT_LOG_INGEST_SECRET=same-as-CLIENT_LOG_INGEST_SECRET
# Optional: accept logs without a secret in production (spam risk): CLIENT_LOG_ALLOW_ANONYMOUS_PROD=1
# Optional: append JSON lines on disk (self-hosted `next start`): CLIENT_LOG_FILE=/var/log/creep-client.jsonl
